name: Earthquake
summary: Recent seismic activity has been reported across various regions. A 4.2 magnitude earthquake occurred south of San Francisco in California, while a 3.2 magnitude tremor hit off the Malibu coast. Santa Cruz County also experienced a preliminary 4.2 magnitude earthquake. San Antonio, Texas, felt the impact of an earthquake miles away. Aromas, near Monterey, recorded a 4.4 magnitude earthquake. A 4.2 magnitude earthquake rattled sleepers south of the Bay Area. Northern Washington residents may have felt a tremor, while an earthquake struck the North-South Carolina border as Hurricane Helene approached. Additionally, a 4.2 magnitude earthquake occurred near Watsonville, Santa Cruz, and a 4.6 magnitude earthquake struck off the Northern California coast.
